1. Sudo Misconfiguration ‚Äì Privilege Escalation
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-01
Vulnerability Name	Sudo NOPASSWD Privilege Escalation
Severity	Critical
CVSS	9.8 (High impact local privilege escalation)
Affected Component	/etc/sudoers configuration
How Vulnerability Occurs	User ‚Äúdaniel‚Äù is allowed to execute /usr/bin/vim as root without password authentication.
Why It Occurs	Misconfigured sudoers file granting excessive privileges.
Exploitation Requirements	Valid local account with sudo rights.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Abuse allowed sudo command to spawn a root shell using vim‚Äôs shell escape functionality.
Impact (CIA)	Full compromise of Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability
Business Risk	Complete system takeover by authenticated attacker.
Remediation	Remove NOPASSWD directive; restrict sudo commands; apply principle of least privilege.
Validation Method	Run sudo -l and verify restricted privileges.
üî¥ 2. Writable Cron-Executed Python Script
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-02
Vulnerability Name	Insecure File Permission ‚Äì Writable Scheduled Script
Severity	High
CVSS	8.8
Affected Component	query.py
How Vulnerability Occurs	Python script executed every 2 minutes is writable by group ‚Äúadministrators.‚Äù
Why It Occurs	Improper file permission configuration.
Exploitation Requirements	User membership in administrators group.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Modify script to execute malicious commands that run in higher privilege context.
Impact (CIA)	Privilege escalation; code execution
Business Risk	Persistent root-level access and system compromise.
Remediation	Restrict file permissions to root-only (chmod 750 or stricter).
Validation Method	Check file ownership and permission using ls -l.
üü† 3. Outdated Ubuntu Packages
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-03
Vulnerability Name	Multiple Outdated System Packages
Severity	High
CVSS	Varies
Affected Component	Ubuntu OS packages
How Vulnerability Occurs	Installed packages contain known CVEs.
Why It Occurs	System not patched regularly.
Exploitation Requirements	Remote or local access depending on vulnerability.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Potentially
High-Level Exploitation Method	Exploit known CVEs affecting installed services.
Impact (CIA)	Remote code execution, denial of service, data exposure
Business Risk	Increased attack surface.
Remediation	Run apt update && apt upgrade; implement patch management policy.
Validation Method	Compare package versions with vendor security advisories.
üü† 4. Apache Version Disclosure
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-04
Vulnerability Name	Web Server Version Disclosure
Severity	Medium
CVSS	5.3
Affected Component	Apache HTTP Server
How Vulnerability Occurs	Server header reveals Apache version.
Why It Occurs	Default Apache configuration.
Exploitation Requirements	Network access to port 80.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Use disclosed version to identify targeted exploits.
Impact (CIA)	Facilitates targeted attack planning
Business Risk	Easier exploitation of known vulnerabilities
Remediation	Disable server tokens; hide version info.
Validation Method	Check HTTP response headers.
üü° 5. SSH Password Authentication Enabled
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-05
Vulnerability Name	SSH Weak Authentication Configuration
Severity	Medium
CVSS	5.8
Affected Component	SSH service
How Vulnerability Occurs	Password-based authentication enabled.
Why It Occurs	Default SSH configuration.
Exploitation Requirements	Valid credentials or brute force attempt.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Credential reuse attack.
Impact (CIA)	Unauthorized access
Business Risk	Increased likelihood of compromise.
Remediation	Disable password authentication; use key-based login.
Validation Method	Check sshd_config.
‚úÖ Important: For Tab Nabbing

Nessus will NOT detect Tab Nabbing because:

It is a web application logic vulnerability

Requires manual testing

Modern browsers mitigate it

You should add it manually in Excel:

üî¥ 6. Tab Nabbing Phishing Vulnerability (Manual Finding)
Field	Content
Vulnerability ID	VULN-06
Vulnerability Name	Tab Nabbing Phishing Attack
Severity	High
CVSS	7.4
Affected Component	Web Application
How Vulnerability Occurs	External links open in new tab without rel="noopener noreferrer".
Why It Occurs	Improper link handling in HTML anchor tags.
Exploitation Requirements	Admin must click malicious link.
Does It Meet Exploitation Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Redirect original tab to fake login page to harvest credentials.
Impact (CIA)	Credential theft; unauthorized SSH access
Business Risk	Full attack chain leading to root compromise
Remediation	Add rel="noopener noreferrer" to external links.
Validation Method	Review HTML source code.

SHEET 1 ‚Äî Vulnerability Register

Create these columns:

| Vuln ID | Vulnerability Name | Severity | Category | Affected Component | How It Occurs | Why It Occurs (Root Cause) | Exploitation Requirements | Meets Exploit Requirements? | High-Level Exploitation Method | Access Gained | Impact | Remediation |

üî¥ VULN-01 ‚Äî Tab Nabbing Phishing
Field	Content
Vuln ID	VULN-01
Vulnerability Name	Tab Nabbing (Phishing via window.opener)
Severity	High
Category	Web Application
Affected Component	Blog external link functionality
How It Occurs	External links open in new tab without rel="noopener noreferrer", allowing manipulation of original tab.
Why It Occurs	Insecure HTML anchor implementation.
Exploitation Requirements	Admin must click submitted link.
Meets Exploit Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Redirect original tab to fake login page to harvest credentials.
Access Gained	Admin credentials
Impact	Credential compromise, unauthorized access
Remediation	Add rel="noopener noreferrer"; implement anti-phishing protections
üî¥ VULN-02 ‚Äî Credential Reuse
Field	Content
Vuln ID	VULN-02
Vulnerability Name	Credential Reuse Across Services
Severity	High
Category	Authentication Weakness
Affected Component	SSH Service
How It Occurs	Same password used for web login and SSH login.
Why It Occurs	Poor credential management policy.
Exploitation Requirements	Stolen credentials.
Meets Exploit Requirements?	Yes
High-Level Exploitation Method	Use harvested credentials to authenticate via SSH.
Access Gained	Remote shell (daniel user)
Impact	Unauthorized system access
Remediation	Enforce unique passwords; implement MFA
