‚úÖ SHEET 2 ‚Äî Attack Chain Summary (Very Important)

Create columns:

| Stage | Vulnerability Used | Access Level | Description | Result |

Fill like this:

Stage	Vulnerability Used	Access Level	Description	Result
1	Tab Nabbing	Credential Theft	Admin tricked into entering credentials on fake page	Credentials obtained
2	Credential Reuse	SSH Access	Reused credentials to authenticate remotely	Shell as daniel
3	Writable Script	Code Execution	Modified cron-executed script	Reverse shell
4	Sudo Misconfiguration	Root	Executed vim as root without password	Full root compromise
‚úÖ SHEET 3 ‚Äî Root Compromise Summary

You can add one final row:

Final Impact	Full System Compromise
Root Access Achieved	Yes
Attack Complexity	Low once credentials obtained
Exploit Chain Required	Yes (Multi-stage)
Business Risk	Complete infrastructure takeover
